contentrichtext.text: '''GGT''' may refer to: * [[Gamma-glutamyl transpeptidase]], an enzyme that catalyzes the reaction between a peptide and an amino acid * [[Glutathione hydrolase]], an enzyme hydrolises glutathione * [[Golden Gate Transit]], a San Francisco Bay Area public transportation system * [[Exuma International Airport]] (IATA code) * [[Genetic code]] for [[Glycine]] according to the [[DNA codon table]] == See also == * [[Galactolipid galactosyltransferase]] (GGGT), an enzyme in glycerolipid metabolism {{Disambiguation}}
